'''麥凱布－蒂勒方法'''（{{lang-en|McCabe–Thiele method}}）被視為分析雙成份[[蒸餾|蒸餾]]最簡易且最具啟發性的方法。<ref>{{cite book|author1=McCabe, W. L.  |author2=Smith, J. C. |lastauthoramp=yes |title=[[Unit_Operations_of_Chemical_Engineering|Unit Operations of Chemical Engineering]]|edition=3rd| publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=1976|isbn=0-07-044825-6}}</ref><ref name=Perry>{{cite book|author1=Perry, Robert H.  |author2=Green, Don W. |lastauthoramp=yes |title=[[Perry's_Chemical_Engineers'_Handbook|Perry's Chemical Engineers' Handbook]]|edition=6th| publisher=McGraw-Hill|year=1984|isbn=0-07-049479-7}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=Beychok|first=Milton|title= Algebraic Solution of McCabe-Thiele Diagram|journal=Chemical Engineering Progress|date= May 1951}}</ref>本方法利用於每個[[理論板數|理論塔板]]（[[氣液平衡|氣液平衡]]板）上的組成皆可由其中一成分之[[摩尔分数|摩尔分数]]決定，且建立在等摩尔流率的假設之上。欲達成等摩尔流率之假設，則需滿足下列條件：
*兩進料成分之[[汽化熱|汽化熱]]需相等。
*每[[摩尔|摩尔]]液體蒸發，必有一摩尔氣體凝結。
*忽略[[溶解熱|溶解熱]]。
本方法由[[沃倫·李·麥凱布|沃倫·李·麥凱布]]及[[歐內斯特·蒂勒|歐內斯特·蒂勒]]兩人率先於1925年發表。<ref>{{cite journal|author1=W.L. McCabe|author2=E.W. Thiele|lastauthoramp=yes|title=Graphical Design Of Fractionating Columns|journal=Industrial and Engineering Chemistry|date=June 1925|volume=17|pages=605–611|url=http://www.aiche-chicago.org/oldsite/Awards/McCabeThieleGraphicalDesignOfFractionatingColumns.pdf|doi=10.1021/ie50186a023|author=|access-date=2016-09-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304031555/http://www.aiche-chicago.org/oldsite/Awards/McCabeThieleGraphicalDesignOfFractionatingColumns.pdf|archive-date=2016-03-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>當時，麥凱布與蒂勒兩人都在[[麻省理工學院|麻省理工學院]]任教。蒂勒於該年完成科學博士學位，並從該校畢業。<ref>Jonathan H. Worstell (March 2009), [http://www.aiche-chicago.org/oldsite/Awards/ThielePresentation.pdf Ernest W. Thiele: His Impact on Chemical Engineering] {{Wayback|url=http://www.aiche-chicago.org/oldsite/Awards/ThielePresentation.pdf |date=20160303211217 }}</ref>至於擁有[[密西根大學|密西根大學]]碩士的麥凱布則在麻省理工學院擔任預約教員，隨後返回密西根大學，並於1928年取得其博士學位。<ref>Ralph E. Fadum (1984), [http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=565&page=193 Warren Lee McCabe] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=565&page=193 |date=20141208123612 }} in ''Memorial Tributes: National Academy of Engineering'', Volume 2.</ref>

